node.title: Seth Meyers Skewers Subpoenaed Trump Cronies
node.alt: “And, believe me, I’m as shocked as you are that these misshapen potato chips had a plan,” Seth Meyers said on Wednesday night.
node.description: “It’s also important to remember these people only hang out with each other because there is no one else who will hang out with them,” Meyers said.
node.content: ["Welcome to Best of Late Night, a rundown of the previous night\u2019s highlights that lets you sleep \u2014 and lets us get paid to watch comedy. Here are the 50 best movies on Netflix right now.", "Seth Meyers gave an update on Donald Trump\u2019s cronies on Wednesday\u2019s \u201cCloser Look.\u201d", "Meyers noted that the congressional committee investigating the Jan. 6 insurrection had subpoenaed five more Trump allies this week, \u201cincluding disgraced right-wing conspiracy theorist Alex Jones, who always looks like he\u2019s trying to Hulk out even though he wasn\u2019t exposed to gamma rays, and Roger Stone, the guy who famously showed up to Trump\u2019s inauguration looking like an 18th-century oil baron that makes his own meth at home.\u201d", "Keke Palmer did impersonations of Cher, Angela Bassett and Shakira on \u201cThe Tonight Show.\u201d", "A new Baby Yoda balloon will fly above the streets of New York at the Macy\u2019s Thanksgiving Day Parade."]
